Title


Traiectum ad Mosam (detail)


Description


English:  Centre: so-called "city virgin" (Dutch: stedemaagd) with coat of arms of the city of Maastricht (Latin: "Traiectum ad Mosam"). Left and right: coats of arms of the Prince-Bishops of Liège (left) and the Dukes of Brabant (right). Detail of a panorama of Maastricht, first published in 1575 (and reprinted multiple times) in Part 2 of Braun & Hogenberg's atlas of world cities Civitates orbis terrarum. Based on a drawing/sketch by the Maastricht canon Simon de Bellomonte, c. 1570.
